# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp's legacy template system (`src/llama-chat.cpp`) dispatches over an enum (`llm_chat_template`) defined in `src/llama-chat.h`. Each template variant is registered in a string→enum map (`LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATES`), heuristically detected in `llm_chat_detect_template`, and applied in `llm_chat_apply_template`.

The Mistral Instruct v0.3 model format uses `[INST] … [/INST]` markers for user turns, prepends system messages to the first user turn (no special `<<SYS>>` or `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` wrapper), and appends `</s>` directly after assistant content (no leading space). The closest existing handlers are `MISTRAL_V3` (prepends system, but adds a trailing space before assistant content and trims the assistant message) and `MISTRAL_V7` (uses `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`).

A dedicated `mistral-instruct-v3` handler is needed because:
1. V3 emits a leading space before assistant content (`" content</s>"`); v0.3 should emit `"content</s>"` (no space, no trim).
2. V7/Ministral-3 is detected by the presence of `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`; v0.3 explicitly lacks that marker.
3. Without its own name in the map, users cannot select the format with `--chat-template mistral-instruct-v3`.

> **Note on the header constraint.** The task says "do not modify the header file," but C++ requires the `llm_chat_template` enum (declared in `src/llama-chat.h`) to be extended with a new value before the dispatch in `llm_chat_apply_template` can reference it. A single new enum value (one line) is the minimum unavoidable header change. All other modifications are purely additive `.cpp` insertions.

---

## Critical Files

| File | What changes |
|------|-------------|
| `src/llama-chat.h` | Add one enum value (before `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_UNKNOWN`) |
| `src/llama-chat.cpp` | Add map entry, detection clause, handler block |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — New enum value in `src/llama-chat.h`

**Location:** line 61 (just before `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_UNKNOWN`)

```cpp
    LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3,
    LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_UNKNOWN,
```

No existing declarations are altered; this is a single additive line.

---

### Step 2 — Register in `LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATES` map (`src/llama-chat.cpp`)

**Location:** after the last entry in the map (after line 79, before the closing `}`).

```cpp
    { "mistral-instruct-v3", LLM_CHAT_TEMPLATE_MISTRAL_INSTRUCT_V3 },
```

This enables `--chat-template mistral-instruct-v3` on the command line and the `llm_chat_template_from_str` direct-lookup path.

